<head /> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="1" /><figure entity="NW_RichTimesD_021_065_001"> <figDesc>Page image of Daily Dispatch, Volume <num value="21">21</num>, <num value="65">Number 65</num>, <ref n="page 1" targOrder="U">page 1</ref>. </figDesc> </figure></p> </div1> <titlePage> <docTitle><titlePart type="main"> Daily Dispatch </titlePart> </docTitle> <docImprint> Vol. Xxi — no.<num value="65">65</num> <pubPlace> <placeName reg="Richmond, Richmond, Virginia" key="tgn,7013964" authname="tgn,7013964">Richmond, Va.</placeName> </pubPlace> <date value="1862-03-18" authname="1862-03-18">Tuesday, March 18, 1862</date> <persName n="Price,,,,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00001" reg="mostcommon:Price,nomatch:0" authname="price"><surname full="yes">Price</surname></persName> <num value="1">one</num> Cent </docImprint> </titlePage> 
<div1 type="subscription" org="uniform" sample="complete"> 
<head><orgName n="Richmond Dispatch" type="newspaper">Richmond Dispatch</orgName><lb /> by <persName n="Cowardin,,,,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00002" reg="mostcommon:Cowardin,nomatch:0" authname="cowardin"><surname full="yes">Cowardin</surname></persName> &amp; <persName n="Hammersley,,,,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00003" reg="mostcommon:Hammersley,nomatch:0" authname="hammersley"><surname full="yes">Hammersley</surname></persName>.</head> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="2" />the <rs>Daily Dispatch</rs> is served to subscribers at <num value="6.25">six and A Quarter</num> Cents per week, payable to the <name>Carrier</name> weekly.

<milestone unit="sentence" n="3" /><persName n="Price,,,,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00004" reg="mostcommon:Price,nomatch:0" authname="price"><surname full="yes">Price</surname></persName> for mailing, <measure n="4dollars" type="currency">$4</measure> a year, or <measure n="2.50dollars" type="currency">$2.50</measure> for <measure n="6months" type="date">six months</measure>, in advance.</p> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="4" />the <rs>Semi-Weekly Dispatch</rs> is issued every <dateStruct full="yes"><day type="name" full="yes">Tuesday</day></dateStruct> and <dateStruct full="yes"><day type="name" full="yes">Friday</day></dateStruct> at <measure n="2.00dollars" type="currency">$2.00</measure>, in advance.</p> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="5" />the <rs>Weekly Dispatch</rs> is issued every <dateStruct full="yes"><day type="name" full="yes">Friday</day></dateStruct>, and mailed to subscribers at <measure n="1dollars" type="currency">$1</measure> per annum.</p> </div1> 
<div1 type="advertising" org="uniform" sample="complete"> 
<head><orgName n="Richmond Dispatch" type="newspaper">Richmond Dispatch</orgName></head> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="6" /> 
<table rows="4" cols="4"> 
<head rend="italics">Terms of Advertising.</head> 
<row role="data"><cell role="data" rows="1" cols="1"><num value="1">1</num> square, <num value="1">1</num> day,</cell><cell role="data" rows="1" cols="1"><measure n="0.50dollars" type="currency">$0.50</measure></cell><cell role="data" rows="1" cols="1"><num value="1">1</num> square, <measure n="5days" type="date">5 days</measure>,</cell><cell role="data" rows="1" cols="1"><measure n="1.00dollars" type="currency">$1.00</measure></cell></row> 
<row role="data"><cell role="data" rows="1" cols="1"><num value="1">1</num> square, <measure n="2days" type="date">2 days</measure></cell><cell role="data" rows="1" cols="1"><measure n="0.75dollars" type="currency">$0.75</measure></cell><cell role="data" rows="1" cols="1"><num value="1">1</num> square, <measure n="5days" type="date">5 days</measure>,</cell><cell role="data" rows="1" cols="1"><measure n="1.75dollars" type="currency">$1.75</measure></cell></row> 
<row role="data"><cell role="data" rows="1" cols="1"><num value="1">1</num> square <measure n="3days" type="date">3 days</measure></cell><cell role="data" rows="1" cols="1"><measure n="1.00dollars" type="currency">$1.00</measure></cell><cell role="data" rows="1" cols="1"><num value="1">1</num> square, <measure n="12days" type="date">12 days</measure>,</cell><cell role="data" rows="1" cols="1"><measure n="3.00dollars" type="currency">$3.00</measure></cell></row> 
<row role="data"><cell role="data" rows="1" cols="1"><num value="1">1</num> square <measure n="4days" type="date">4 days</measure></cell><cell role="data" rows="1" cols="1"><measure n="1.36dollars" type="currency">$1.36</measure></cell><cell role="data" rows="1" cols="1"><num value="1">1</num> square, <dateStruct value="-1-" full="yes" authname="--01"><month reg="1" full="yes">1 month</month></dateStruct>,</cell><cell role="data" rows="1" cols="1"><measure n="5.00dollars" type="currency">$5.00</measure></cell></row> </table></p> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="7" /><hi rend="italics">Larger advertisements in exact properties.</hi></p> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="8" />Advertisements published until forbid, will be charged <measure n="50cents" type="currency">50 cents</measure> per square of <num value="8">eight</num> lines for the <num value="1" type="ordinal">first</num> insertion, and <measure n="25cents" type="currency">25 cents</measure> for each continuance</p> </div1> </front> <body> <milestone unit="column" n="1" /> 
<div1 type="notices" org="uniform" sample="complete"> 
<head /> 
<div2 type="military" org="uniform" sample="complete"> 
<head>Military notices.</head> 
<div3 type="orders" n="1" org="uniform" sample="complete"> 
<head>Attention!

<milestone unit="sentence" n="9" /><num value="2" type="ordinal">Second</num> Military Class!</head> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="10" /> In pursuance of the <name>Proclamation</name> of the <rs>Governor</rs> of <placeName reg="Virginia, United States, North and Central America" key="tgn,7007919" authname="tgn,7007919">Virginia</placeName> of the <date value="03-18" authname="--03-18">18th March,</date> calling outs special force from certain cities and corporations, for the defence of the <rs>State</rs>.

<milestone unit="sentence" n="11" /><q direct="unspecified">"all the white male inhabitants of the city of <placeName key="tgn,7013964" n="1.000 11" reg="richmond, richmond, virginia" authname="tgn,7013964">Richmond</placeName> who reside in and around it, within <measure n="1mile" type="distance">one mile</measure> of the corporation line, on the north side of <placeName reg="Richmond, Richmond, Virginia" key="tgn,7013964" authname="tgn,7013964">James river</placeName>,"</q> and who are between the ages of <num value="16">sixteen</num> and <num value="18">eighteen</num> and <num value="45">forty-five</num> and <measure n="55years" type="date">fifty-five years</measure>, except such as are exempt by law from all military duty, are required to assemble for enrollment and organization as the military of the <num value="2" type="ordinal">second</num> class, at the times and places hereinafter mentioned.

<milestone unit="sentence" n="12" />It is hoped that all will cheerfully and promptly respond to this call, that a large and effective <orgName n="Reserve Corps" type="corps">reserve corps</orgName> may be speedily organized.

<milestone unit="sentence" n="13" />The young men will be formed into companies separate from the older men, and each company will elect its own officers.--Young men under <num value="16">sixteen</num>, able to hear arms, will be admitted into the ranks.

<milestone unit="sentence" n="14" />All the youth of this character in the district are <unclear /> invited to come forward and prepare themselves for the service of their country. </p> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="15" /> The Commissioners of the <name>Revenue</name> for the city and county will meet at the places appointed in their respective districts, to aid in the enrollment. </p> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="16" /> All persons embraced in this call, residing in the city, west of <address><street n="7 Street">7th street</street></address> and <measure n="1mile" type="distance">one mile</measure> beyond the corporate limits west of <address><street n="7 Street">7th street</street></address> extended north, will assemble at the <hi rend="smallcaps"><num value="2" type="ordinal">Second</num> <placeName reg="Visitable Market">Visitable Market</placeName>,</hi> at <time value="3pm">3 o'clock P. M.</time> On <dateStruct full="yes"><day type="name" full="yes">Tuesday</day></dateStruct>, <date value="1862-03-18" authname="1862-03-18">March 18th, 1862</date> <unclear /> enrollment. </p> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="17" /> All residing between <address><street n="7 Street">7th</street></address> and <address><street n="14 Street">14th streets</street></address>, and <measure n="1mile" type="distance">one mile</measure> beyond the corporate limits, between the line of these streets extended north, will assemble in front of the <hi rend="smallcaps"><unclear /> <persName n="Hill,,,,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00005" reg="mostcommon:Hill,nomatch:0" authname="hill"><surname full="yes">Hill</surname></persName>,</hi> on <name>Capitol</name> street, on <dateStruct full="yes"><day type="name" full="yes">Wednesday</day></dateStruct>, <date value="1862-03-19" authname="1862-03-19">March 19th, 1862,</date> at <time value="3pm">3 o'clock P. M.</time> </p> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="18" /> All residing east of <address><street n="14 Street">14th street</street></address> and <measure n="1mile" type="distance">one mile</measure> beyond the corporate limits east of <address><street n="14 Street">14th st</street></address>. extended north, will assemble in <hi rend="smallcaps">Military Fill,</hi> over First Market, on <dateStruct full="yes"><day type="name" full="yes">Thursday</day></dateStruct>, <date value="1862-03-20" authname="1862-03-20">March 20, 1862,</date> at <unclear><num value="5">5</num></unclear> o'clock P. M. </p> <closer> By order of <signed>the <rs>Governor</rs>.</signed> <lb /> <signed><persName n="Ellyson,,H.,K.,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00006" reg="default:Ellyson,H.,K.,," authname="ellyson,h.,k."><foreName full="yes">H.</foreName> <foreName full="yes">K.</foreName>  <surname full="yes">Ellyson</surname></persName>,</signed> <lb /> <rs type="role" reg="Sheriff">Sheriff</rs> of the <rs type="place">City of Richmond</rs>. <lb /> mh <num value="17">17</num>--4t* </closer> </div3> 
<div3 type="orders" n="2" org="uniform" sample="complete"> 
<head>Headq's Dep't of <placeName reg="Henrico, Virginia, United States" key="tgn,1002467" authname="tgn,1002467">Henrico</placeName>, <hi rend="smallcaps"><placeName reg="Richmond, Richmond, Virginia" key="tgn,7013964" authname="tgn,7013964">Richmond, Va.</placeName>,</hi> <date value="1862-03-15" authname="1862-03-15">March 15, 1862.</date><lb />General orders, no. <unclear /></head> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="19" /> I. The practice of fast driving and riding through the city endangers the safety of the people, and is, therefore, prohibited.

<milestone unit="sentence" n="20" />The speed for omnibuses, <rs n="light carriages" type="product">light carriages</rs>, and horseback-riding, is at the rate of <measure n="5miles" type="distance">five miles</measure> per hour; wagons carts, and other vehicles for freight, will be driven at a walk, whether loaded or unloaded.

<milestone unit="sentence" n="21" />The police and patrol are charged with the execution of this order, and will arrest every <num value="1">one</num> who may violate it no matter what his rank or position.

<milestone unit="sentence" n="22" />If the driver on rider be a white man, he will be confined and brought before a court-martial; if a negro, he will immediately receive, for the <num value="1" type="ordinal">first</num> offence, <num value="39">39</num> lashes; for the <num value="2" type="ordinal">second</num> and every succeeding offence, <num value="50">50</num> lashes. </p> <closer> <signed><persName n="Winder,,John,H.,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00007" reg="default:Winder,John,H.,," authname="winder,john,h."><foreName full="yes">John</foreName> <foreName full="yes">H.</foreName>  <surname full="yes">Winder</surname></persName>,</signed> <lb /> <signed><rs type="role" reg="Brigadier-General">Brig.-Gen.</rs> Commanding,</signed> &amp;c. <lb /> mh <num value="17">17</num>--1w </closer> </div3> 
<div3 type="orders" n="3" org="uniform" sample="complete"> 
<head><orgName type="mil" key="HvArtillery">Heavy Artillery</orgName>. <measure n="50dollars" type="currency">$50</measure> bounty, and uniforms furnished.</head> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="23" /> The undersigned are authorized by the <rs type="role" reg="Secretary of War">Secretary of War</rs> to raise a Company for the <orgName n="Heavy Artillery" type="artillery">heavy Artillery</orgName> service.

<milestone unit="sentence" n="24" />We have been for the past <measure n="11months" type="date">eleven months</measure> in active service as <rs type="role" reg="Lieutenant">Lieutenants</rs> of such a company, and have already a number of men enlisted. </p> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="25" /> All who desire to join us will please apply at our recruiting office, <num value="17">No. 17</num>, <address><street n="Main street">Main street</street></address>, up stairs, to <persName n="Lawson,,William,,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00008" reg="default:Lawson,William,,," authname="lawson,william"><foreName n="William" full="yes">Wm.</foreName> <surname full="yes">Lawson</surname></persName>, <orgName type="company" n="Company H">Company H</orgName>, <orgName type="regiment" key="1VAVolunteer">First Regiment Virginia Volunteers</orgName>, or at our Camp in <placeName reg="Yorktown, York, Virginia" key="tgn,2115169" authname="tgn,2115169">Yorktown</placeName>. </p> <closer> <signed><persName n="Jackson,,Thomas,G.,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00009" reg="default:Jackson,Thomas,G.,," authname="jackson,thomas,g."><foreName full="yes">Thomas</foreName> <foreName full="yes">G.</foreName>  <surname full="yes">Jackson</surname></persName>,</signed> <lb /> mh <num value="17">17</num>--1m* <signed><persName n="Lawson,,Thomas,,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00010" reg="default:Lawson,Thomas,,," authname="lawson,thomas"><foreName full="yes">Thomas</foreName>  <surname full="yes">Lawson</surname></persName>.</signed> </closer> </div3> 
<div3 type="orders" n="4" org="uniform" sample="complete"> 
<head><orgName type="mil" key="HvArtillery">Heavy Artillery</orgName>.</head> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="26" /> I am authorized by the <rs type="role" reg="Secretary of War">Secretary of War</rs> to raise a battalion of <orgName type="mil" key="HvArtillery">Heavy Artillery</orgName> for the defence of <placeName reg="Richmond, Richmond, Virginia" key="tgn,7013964" authname="tgn,7013964">James river</placeName>. <num value="1">One</num> more company wanted to complete the battalion — if offered at once will be received — at <placeName reg="Jamestown Island, James City, Virginia" key="tgn,1007534" authname="tgn,1007534">Jamestown Island</placeName>. </p> <closer> mh <num value="17">17</num>--1w* <signed><persName n="Allan,Captain,William,,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00011" reg="default:Allan,William,,," authname="allan,william"><foreName n="William" full="yes">Wm.</foreName> <surname full="yes">Allan</surname>, <roleName n="Captain" full="yes">Capt.</roleName></persName></signed> </closer> </div3> 
<div3 type="orders" n="5" org="uniform" sample="complete"> 
<head>Attention!<lb /><persName n="Wise,,,,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00012" reg="mostcommon:Wise,Henry,A.,,:1" authname="wise,henry,a."><surname full="yes">Wise</surname></persName> mounted Guard.</head> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="27" /> All members of this company will report themselves at camp, <placeName reg="Howards Grove, Rockingham, New Hampshire" key="tgn,2403820" authname="tgn,2403820">Howard's Grove</placeName>, on <dateStruct full="yes"><day type="name" full="yes">Tuesday</day></dateStruct> <time>morning</time> at <time value="10oclock">10 o'clock</time>. Every member is requested to be punctual in attendance, as election of officers will be held. </p> <closer> <signed><persName n="Hawley,Lieutenant,L.,J.,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00013" reg="default:Hawley,L.,J.,," authname="hawley,l.,j."><roleName n="Lieutenant" full="yes">Lieut.</roleName> <foreName full="yes">L.</foreName> <foreName full="yes">J.</foreName> <surname full="yes">Hawley</surname></persName>,</signed> <lb /> mh <num value="17">17</num>--2t* <signed>Wise Legion.</signed> </closer> </div3> 
<div3 type="orders" n="6" org="uniform" sample="complete"> 
<head type="nobreak">Military notice</head> 
<p rend="nobreak">

<milestone unit="sentence" n="28" /> --Members of the <orgName n="Otey Battery" type="battery">Otey Battery</orgName> will report <dateStruct full="yes"><day type="name" full="yes">Wednesday</day></dateStruct>, for duty at the company Headquarters, <address><street n="Pearl Street 13">No. 13 Pearl street</street></address>. Members in the country will come prepared to go into camp. </p> <closer> By order. <lb /> mh <num value="17">17</num>--3t* <signed><persName n="Otey,,G.,G.,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00014" reg="default:Otey,G.,G.,," authname="otey,g.,g."><foreName full="yes">G.</foreName> <foreName full="yes">G.</foreName>  <surname full="yes">Otey</surname></persName>, <rs type="role2">Captain</rs>.</signed> </closer> </div3> 
<div3 type="orders" n="7" org="uniform" sample="complete"> 
<head><orgName n="War Department" type="department">War Department</orgName>,<hi rend="smallcaps">Adj't and Insp's Gen.'s office,</hi> <placeName key="tgn,7013964" n="1.000 11" reg="richmond, richmond, virginia" authname="tgn,7013964">Richmond</placeName>, <date value="1862-03-14" authname="1862-03-14">March 14, 1862.</date> <lb />General orders, <num value="15">no. 15</num>:</head> 
<list type="ordered"> 
<head /> 
<item n="1"> I. The following Proclamation is published for the information of all concerned: <lb /> proclamation.

<milestone unit="sentence" n="29" /><lb /> By virtue of the power vested in me by law in declare the suspension of the privilege of the writ of <hi rend="italics">habeas corpus,</hi> J, <persName n="Davis,,Jefferson,,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00015" reg="default:Davis,Jefferson,,," authname="davis,jefferson"><foreName full="yes">Jefferson</foreName> <surname full="yes">Davis</surname></persName>, <rs type="role" reg="President">President</rs> of the <placeName reg="United States" key="tgn,7012149" authname="tgn,7012149">Confederate States of America</placeName>, do proclaim that <persName n="Law,,Martial,,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00016" reg="default:Law,Martial,,," authname="law,martial"><foreName full="yes">Martial</foreName> <surname full="yes">Law</surname></persName> is hereby extended over the counties of <placeName reg="Elizabeth City, Pasquotank, North Carolina" key="tgn,2074494" authname="tgn,2074494">Elizabeth City</placeName>, <persName n="York,,,,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00017" reg="mostcommon:York,nomatch:0" authname="york"><surname full="yes">York</surname></persName>, <persName n="Warwick,,,,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00018" reg="mostcommon:Warwick,nomatch:0" authname="warwick"><surname full="yes">Warwick</surname></persName>, <placeName reg="Gloucester, Gloucester, Virginia" key="tgn,2111950" authname="tgn,2111950">Gloucester</placeName>, and <persName n="Mathews,,,,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00019" reg="mostcommon:Mathews,nomatch:0" authname="mathews"><surname full="yes">Mathews</surname></persName>; and I do proclaim the suspension of all civil jurisdiction, (with the exception of that enabling the courts to take cognizance of the probate of wills, the administration of the estates of deceased persons, the qualifications of guardians, to enter decrees and orders for the partition and sale of property, to make orders concerning roads and bridges, to assess county levies, and to order the payment of county dues,) and the suspension of the privilege of the writ of <hi rend="italics">habeas corpus</hi> in the counties aforesaid.

<milestone unit="sentence" n="30" /><lb /> In faith whereof I have hereinto signed my name and set my seal, this <dateStruct value="-03-14" full="yes" authname="--03-14"><day reg="14" full="yes">fourteenth</day> day of <month reg="03" full="yes">March</month></dateStruct>, in the year <dateStruct value="1862" full="yes" authname="1862"><year reg="1862" full="yes">one thousand eight hundred and sixty-two</year></dateStruct>. <lb /> <persName n="Davis,,Jefferson,,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00020" reg="default:Davis,Jefferson,,," authname="davis,jefferson"><foreName full="yes">Jefferson</foreName> <surname full="yes">Davis</surname></persName>.

<milestone unit="sentence" n="31" /><lb /> </item> 
<item n="2"> <num value="2">II</num>. <hi rend="smallcaps"><persName n="Magruder,Major-General,,,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00021" reg="mostcommon:Magruder,J.,B.,,:1" authname="magruder,j.,b."><roleName n="Major-General" full="yes">Major-General</roleName> <surname full="yes">Magruder</surname></persName>,</hi> commanding the <orgName n="Army of the Peninsula" type="army">Army of the Peninsula</orgName>, is charged with the due execution of the foregoing Proclamation.

<milestone unit="sentence" n="32" />He will forthwith establish an efficient military police, and will enforce the following orders: All distillation of spirituous liquors is positively prohibited, and the distilleries will forthwith be closed.

<milestone unit="sentence" n="33" />The sale of spirituous liquors of any kind is also prohibited, and establishments for the sale thereof will be closed.

<milestone unit="sentence" n="34" /></item> 
<item n="3"> <num value="3">III</num>.

<milestone unit="sentence" n="35" />All persons infringing the above prohibition will suffer such punishment as shall be ordered by the sentence of a Court-Martial; provided, that no sentence to hard labor for more than <num value="1">one</num> month shall be inflicted by the sentence of a <orgName n="Regimental Court" type="court">Regimental Court</orgName>-Martial, as directed by the <num value="67" type="ordinal">67th</num> Article of War. </item> </list> <closer> By command of the <rs type="role" reg="Secretary of War">Secretary of War</rs> <lb /> <signed>[Signed] <persName n="Cooper,,S.,,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00022" reg="default:Cooper,S.,,," authname="cooper,s."><foreName full="yes">S.</foreName> <surname full="yes">Cooper</surname></persName>,</signed> <lb /> mh <num value="15">15</num>--1w <signed>Adj't and <rs type="role" reg="Inspector General">Insp. General</rs>.</signed> </closer> </div3> 
<div3 type="orders" n="8" org="uniform" sample="complete"> 
<head rend="smallcaps"><rs type="role">Adj't.</rs> And <placeName reg="Insp's General's office">Insp's General's office</placeName>, <placeName key="tgn,7013964" n="1.000 11" reg="richmond, richmond, virginia" authname="tgn,7013964">Richmond</placeName>, <date value="1862-03-08" authname="1862-03-08">March 8, 1862.</date> <lb />General orders, <num value="11">no. 11</num>.--</head> 
<list type="ordered"> 
<head /> 
<item n="1"> I. The following Proclamation is published for the information of all concerned: <lb /> proclamation.

<milestone unit="sentence" n="36" /><lb /> By virtue of the power vested in me by law to declare the suspension of the privilege of the writ of <hi rend="italics">habeas corpus</hi> in cities threatened with invasion-- <lb /> I, <hi rend="smallcaps"><persName n="Davis,,Jefferson,,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00023" reg="default:Davis,Jefferson,,," authname="davis,jefferson"><foreName full="yes">Jefferson</foreName> <surname full="yes">Davis</surname></persName>,</hi> <rs type="role" reg="President">President</rs> of the <placeName reg="United States" key="tgn,7012149" authname="tgn,7012149">Confederate States of America</placeName>, do proclaim that Martial law is hereby extended over the city of <placeName reg="Petersburg, Petersburg, Virginia" key="tgn,7014404" authname="tgn,7014404">Petersburg</placeName> and the adjoining and surrounding country to the distance of <measure n="10miles" type="distance">ten miles</measure>, and I do proclaim the suspension of all civil jurisdiction, (with the exception of that of the <rs>Mayor</rs> of the city, and that enabling the <rs type="place">Courts</rs> to take cognizance of the probate of wills, the administration of the estates of deceased persons, the qualifications of guardians, to enter decrees and orders for the partition and sale of property, to make orders concerning roads and bridges, to assess county levies, and to order the payment of county dues,) and the suspension of the privilege of the writ of <hi rend="italics">habeas corpus</hi> within the said city and surrounding country to the distance aforesaid.

<milestone unit="sentence" n="37" /><lb /> In faith whereof I have hereunto signed my name and set my seal, on the <dateStruct value="-03-8" full="yes" authname="--03-08"><day reg="8" full="yes">eighth</day> day of <month reg="03" full="yes">March</month></dateStruct>, in the year <dateStruct value="1862" full="yes" authname="1862"><year reg="1862" full="yes">one thousand eight hundred and sixty-two</year></dateStruct>. <lb /> <persName n="Davis,,Jefferson,,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00024" reg="default:Davis,Jefferson,,," authname="davis,jefferson"><foreName full="yes">Jefferson</foreName> <surname full="yes">Davis</surname></persName>.

<milestone unit="sentence" n="38" /><lb /> </item> 
<item n="2"> <num value="2">II</num>. <hi rend="smallcaps"><persName n="Panhill,,William,,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00025" reg="default:Panhill,William,,," authname="panhill,william"><foreName full="yes">William</foreName> <surname full="yes">Panhill</surname></persName></hi> is appointed <rs type="role" reg="Provost Marshal">Provost Marshal</rs>, and is charged with the due execution of the foregoing Proclamation, and will forthwith establish an efficient military police, and will enforce the following orders: <lb /> "All distillation of spirituous liquors is positively prohibited, and the distilleries will forthwith be closed.

<milestone unit="sentence" n="39" />The sale of spirituous liquors of any kind is also prohibited, and establishments for the sale thereof will be closed." </item> 
<item n="3"> <num value="3">III</num>.

<milestone unit="sentence" n="40" />All persons infringing the above prohibition will suffer such punishment as shall be ordered by the sentence of a Court-Martial, provided that no sentence to hard labor for more than <num value="1">one</num> month shall be inflicted by the sentence of a <orgName n="Regimental Court" type="court">Regimental Court</orgName>-Martial, as directed by the <num value="67" type="ordinal">67th</num> Article of War. </item> </list> <closer> By command of the <rs type="role" reg="Secretary of War">Secretary of War</rs>. <lb /> <signed>[Signed,] <persName n="Cooper,,S.,,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00026" reg="default:Cooper,S.,,," authname="cooper,s."><foreName full="yes">S.</foreName> <surname full="yes">Cooper</surname></persName>,</signed> <lb /> mh <num value="11">11</num>--1w <signed><rs type="role">Adjt.</rs> and Insp't. <rs type="role">Gen.</rs></signed> </closer> </div3> <milestone unit="column" n="2" /> 
<div3 type="orders" n="9" org="uniform" sample="complete"> 
<head /> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="41" />Having received authority from the <rs type="role" reg="Secretary of War">Secretary of War</rs> to raise an <orgName n="Independent Battalion" type="battalion">independent battalion</orgName> of <orgName type="mil" key="Light">Light Infantry</orgName>, to be used exclusively as skirmishers and scouts, and to be attached to no other corps, except at the discretion of the <rs type="role" reg="Commander-in-Chief">Commander-in-Chief</rs> of the department in which we may be stationed, in times of great emergency, I call for volunteers from my own and other States--men now in service, or who have not yet enlisted — to come forward at this critical juncture, when the primal glory of our arms is partially collapsed in a temporary gloom, and enroll their names in a corps which will come frequently in contact with the polluters of our soil and the desolator of our homes. </p> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="42" /> I propose to facilitate the organization of the battalion by offering Captaincies to those enlisting not less than <num value="30">thirty</num> men, <num value="1" type="ordinal">1st</num> Lieutenancies to those enlisting <num value="25">twenty-five</num>, <num value="2" type="ordinal">2nd</num> do. to those enlisting <num value="20">twenty</num>. </p> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="43" /> <num value="70">Seventy</num> privates will be the minimum for a company. </p> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="44" /> The usual bounty will, of course, be paid, and subsistence and transportation furnished. </p> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="45" /> For particulars, address me at <placeName reg="Yorktown, York, Virginia" key="tgn,2115169" authname="tgn,2115169">Yorktown</placeName>, or <persName n="Scott,,W.,H.,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00027" reg="default:Scott,W.,H.,," authname="scott,w.,h."><foreName full="yes">W.</foreName> <foreName full="yes">H.</foreName> <surname full="yes">Scott</surname></persName>, Druggist, <placeName reg="Richmond, Richmond, Virginia" key="tgn,7013964" authname="tgn,7013964">Richmond, Va.</placeName> </p> <closer> <signed><persName n="Causey,,Charles,H.,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00028" reg="default:Causey,Charles,H.,," authname="causey,charles,h."><foreName n="Charles" full="yes">Chas.</foreName> <foreName full="yes">H.</foreName>  <surname full="yes">Causey</surname></persName>,</signed> <lb /> mh <num value="11">11</num>--1w* <signed><rs type="role">Lieut.</rs> Cavalry, C. S. A.</signed> </closer> </div3> 
<div3 type="orders" n="10" org="uniform" sample="complete"> 
<head type="nobreak">Attention.</head> 
<p rend="nobreak">

<milestone unit="sentence" n="46" /> --The organization of our company is now nearly completed.

<milestone unit="sentence" n="47" />We have the guns secured and all equipments ready as soon as we are mustered into service.

<milestone unit="sentence" n="48" />Those who do not immediately volunteers will be obliged to go into the militia service.

<milestone unit="sentence" n="49" />The system of substitution has been abandoned by the <rs>Government</rs>, so that all who are bound for service must now represent themselves in person.

<milestone unit="sentence" n="50" />This we announce upon authority.

<milestone unit="sentence" n="51" />We then earnestly invoke those who are willing to share with us the fortunes of this war, who would rather appear voluntarily upon the field in defence of their country than be the reluctant soldiers of coercion, so come forward now, this day, and enlist their names as <hi rend="italics">volunteers</hi> in a great and glorious cause.

<milestone unit="sentence" n="52" />Apply at our office in the <rs>Whig Budding</rs>. </p> <closer> <signed><persName n="Johnson,,Marmaduks,,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00029" reg="default:Johnson,Marmaduks,,," authname="johnson,marmaduks"><foreName full="yes">Marmaduks</foreName>  <surname full="yes">Johnson</surname></persName>,</signed> <lb /> <signed><persName n="Bransford,,John,W.,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00030" reg="default:Bransford,John,W.,," authname="bransford,john,w."><foreName full="yes">John</foreName> <foreName full="yes">W.</foreName>  <surname full="yes">Bransford</surname></persName>,</signed> <lb /> <signed><persName n="Guigon,,A.,B.,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00031" reg="default:Guigon,A.,B.,," authname="guigon,a.,b."><foreName full="yes">A.</foreName> <foreName full="yes">B.</foreName>  <surname full="yes">Guigon</surname></persName>,</signed> <lb /> mh <num value="11">11</num>--ts <signed><persName n="Clutter,,V.,J.,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00032" reg="default:Clutter,V.,J.,," authname="clutter,v.,j."><foreName full="yes">V.</foreName> <foreName full="yes">J.</foreName>  <surname full="yes">Clutter</surname></persName>.</signed> </closer> </div3> 
<div3 type="orders" n="11" org="uniform" sample="complete"> 
<head type="nobreak">Special notice.</head> 
<p rend="nobreak">

<milestone unit="sentence" n="53" /> --The <orgName type="mil" key="InfantryCompany">Infantry Company</orgName> organized at the office of <persName n="Parker,Doctor,,,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00033" reg="mostcommon:Parker,nomatch:0" authname="parker"><roleName n="Doctor" full="yes">Dr.</roleName> <surname full="yes">Parker</surname></persName>, in the <rs type="place">Law Building</rs> having received <hi rend="italics">assurance</hi> of a <q direct="unspecified">"<hi rend="italics">Battery of <orgName type="mil" key="LightArtillery">Light Artillery</orgName>,</hi>"</q> it was unanimously resolved, at a meeting held last <dateStruct full="yes"><day type="name" full="yes">Saturday</day></dateStruct> <time>night</time>, to adopt that arm of the service.

<milestone unit="sentence" n="54" />The guns will be ready in less <measure n="30days" type="date">thirty days</measure>. So soon as the company is fully organized it will go into the <placeName reg="Camp of Instruction">Camp of Instruction</placeName> at the <rs type="place">Fair Grounds</rs>.

<milestone unit="sentence" n="55" />All those disposed to join will report as early as possible, at <placeName><persName n="Parker,Doctor,,,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00034" reg="mostcommon:Parker,nomatch:0" authname="parker"><roleName n="Doctor" full="yes">Dr.</roleName> <surname full="yes">Parker</surname></persName>'s office</placeName>, as the company expects to be mustered in this week.

<milestone unit="sentence" n="56" />Meetings held regularly on <dateStruct full="yes"><day type="name" full="yes">Wednesday</day></dateStruct> and <dateStruct full="yes"><day type="name" full="yes">Saturday</day></dateStruct> nights. </p> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="57" /> mh <num value="11">11</num>--ts </p> </div3> 
<div3 type="orders" n="12" org="uniform" sample="complete"> 
<head /> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="58" />Having been authorized by the <rs type="role" reg="Secretary of War">Secretary of War</rs> to raise a Battalion or a Regiment of <orgName type="mil" key="HvArtillery">Heavy Artillery</orgName>, for <measure n="3years" type="date">three years</measure> or the war, I should be glad to confer with <rs type="role2">Captains</rs> who have companies not yet mustered into the service, and also those who desire to raise companies. </p> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="59" /> Volunteers or recruits enlisting for <measure n="3years" type="date">three years</measure> will receive a bounty of <measure n="50dollars" type="currency">$50</measure>, payable as soon as they are sworn into service and accepted, upon inspection, by a medical officer, together with transportation and subsistence, from the time and place of enlistment, until inspected and mustered. </p> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="60" /> <measure n="12months" type="date">Twelve months</measure> men can re-enlist, singly or by companies for <measure n="2years" type="date">two years</measure> or the war, and receive <measure n="50dollars" type="currency">$50</measure> bounty. </p> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="61" /> To those citizens who have not reported themselves, as required, and who will in a few days be drafted, <hi rend="italics">now</hi> is the time, and the <hi rend="italics">last,</hi> to serve as volunteers. </p> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="62" /> Volunteers will be received singly or by companies, from any portion of the <rs>Confederacy</rs>. </p> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="63" /> Office under the <rs type="place">St. Charles Hotel</rs>, <orgName n="Old Dominion Insurance Company" type="company">Old Dominion Insurance Company</orgName>, <address><street n="Main street">Main street</street></address>. City <orgName n="Post Office" type="office">Post-Office</orgName>, <measure value="Box 877" type="Box">Box 877</measure>. </p> <closer> <signed><persName n="Morriss,,Robert,F.,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00035" reg="default:Morriss,Robert,F.,," authname="morriss,robert,f."><foreName full="yes">Robert</foreName> <foreName full="yes">F.</foreName>  <surname full="yes">Morriss</surname></persName>,</signed> <lb /> <rs type="role2">Colonel</rs> <orgName type="regiment" key="Regiment 179">179th Regiment</orgName>. <lb /> I have the promise of <persName n="Armstrong,,,,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00036" reg="mostcommon:Armstrong,nomatch:0" authname="armstrong"><surname full="yes">Armstrong</surname></persName> field pieces; and should it be realized, this regiment will enter the field as <orgName type="mil" key="LightArtillery">Light Artillery</orgName>. <lb /> mh <num value="6">6</num>--12t* </closer> </div3> 
<div3 type="orders" n="13" org="uniform" sample="complete"> 
<head><orgName n="Department of the Executive" type="government">Executive Department</orgName>,<hi rend="smallcaps"><placeName reg="Richmond, Richmond, Virginia" key="tgn,7013964" authname="tgn,7013964">Richmond, Va.</placeName>,</hi> <date value="1862-03-07" authname="1862-03-07">March 7, 1862.</date></head> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="64" /> all Sheriffs and others collecting State Arms are desired to have the same boxed, marked <q direct="unspecified">"<rs type="role">Col.</rs> C. <hi rend="smallcaps"><persName n="Dimmock,,,,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00037" reg="mostcommon:Dimmock,nomatch:0" authname="dimmock"><surname full="yes">Dimmock</surname></persName>,</hi> <placeName reg="Richmond, Richmond, Virginia" key="tgn,7013964" authname="tgn,7013964">Richmond, Va.</placeName>,"</q> and forwarded as soon as possible.

<milestone unit="sentence" n="65" />The compensation for collecting, and the necessary expenses of transportation to this city, will be paid on the presentation of the receipts of <hi rend="smallcaps"><persName n="Dimmock,Colonel,,,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00038" reg="mostcommon:Dimmock,nomatch:0" authname="dimmock"><roleName n="Colonel" full="yes">Col.</roleName> <surname full="yes">Dimmock</surname></persName>.</hi> </p> <closer> Approved, <signed><persName n="Letches,,John,,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00039" reg="default:Letches,John,,," authname="letches,john"><foreName full="yes">John</foreName>  <surname full="yes">Letches</surname></persName>.</signed> <lb /> City papers copy mh <num value="7">7</num>--1m </closer> </div3> 
<div3 type="orders" n="14" org="uniform" sample="complete"> 
<head /> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="66" /> I Am authorized by the <rs type="role" reg="Secretary of War">Secretary of War</rs> to raise an <orgName type="mil" key="InfantryCompany">Infantry Company</orgName>, and as no more new companies will be accepted until <placeName reg="Virginia, United States, North and Central America" key="tgn,7007919" authname="tgn,7007919">Virginia</placeName>'s quota has been furnished (this company will be counted as a part of it,) this is <num value="1">one</num> of the few last chances to escape the draft; and who would be drafted?

<milestone unit="sentence" n="67" />Men accepted from all parts of the <rs>State</rs> or Confederacy.

<milestone unit="sentence" n="68" /><measure n="12months" type="date">Twelve months</measure> men can <unclear>re-enlist</unclear> with me. <measure n="50dollars" type="currency">$50</measure> bounty paid as soon as inspected.

<milestone unit="sentence" n="69" />Recruiting <placeName reg="office">office</placeName> at the office of the <orgName n="Insurance Company" type="company">Insurance Company of the <placeName reg="Virginia" key="tgn,7007919" authname="tgn,7007919">State of Virginia</placeName></orgName>, under the <rs type="place">American Hotel</rs>, <placeName reg="Richmond, Richmond, Virginia" key="tgn,7013964" authname="tgn,7013964">Richmond, Va.</placeName> Address me. </p> <closer> mh <num value="10">10</num>--ts <signed><persName n="Robins,,W.,B.,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00040" reg="default:Robins,W.,B.,," authname="robins,w.,b."><foreName full="yes">W.</foreName> <foreName full="yes">B.</foreName>  <surname full="yes">Robins</surname></persName>.</signed> </closer> </div3> 
<div3 type="orders" n="15" org="uniform" sample="complete"> 
<head>Recruits — <placeName key="tgn,7013964" n="1.000 11" reg="richmond, richmond, virginia" authname="tgn,7013964">Richmond</placeName> sharp-shooters.</head> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="70" /> <num value="50">Fifty</num> Recruits are wanted to fill up the ranks of this well-known company to the maximum number.

<milestone unit="sentence" n="71" />A bounty of <measure n="50dollars" type="currency">$50</measure> will be paid each recruit, and sustenance commuted until they join the company; pay commences from date of enlistment.

<milestone unit="sentence" n="72" />None but good men need apply, as the company heretofore has sustained an enviable reputation. </p> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="73" /> This company is armed with good Riffes, and has seen as much active service as, any company in the army.

<milestone unit="sentence" n="74" />Application to be made to the undersigned at Star <orgName n="Exchange Bank" type="bank">Exchange, Bank</orgName> street, or to <persName n="Wingfield,Corporal,W.,J.,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00041" reg="default:Wingfield,W.,J.,," authname="wingfield,w.,j."><roleName n="Corporal" full="yes">Corporal</roleName> <foreName full="yes">W.</foreName> <foreName full="yes">J.</foreName> <surname full="yes">Wingfield</surname></persName>. </p> <closer> <signed><persName n="Prisst,,E.,E.,De," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00042" reg="default:Prisst,E.,E.,De," authname="prisst,e.,e.,de"><foreName full="yes">E.</foreName> <foreName full="yes">E.</foreName>  <foreName full="yes">De</foreName>  <surname full="yes">Prisst</surname></persName>,</signed> <lb /> mh <num value="2">2</num>--1m* <rs type="role">Lieut.</rs> and Recruiting Officer. </closer> </div3> 
<div3 type="orders" n="16" org="uniform" sample="complete"> 
<head>Headq's Dep't of <placeName reg="Henrico, Virginia, United States" key="tgn,1002467" authname="tgn,1002467">Henrico</placeName>,<hi rend="smallcaps"><placeName key="tgn,7013964" n="1.000 11" reg="richmond, richmond, virginia" authname="tgn,7013964">Richmond</placeName>,</hi> <placeName reg="Virginia" key="tgn,7007919" authname="tgn,7007919">Va.</placeName>, <date value="1862-03-12" authname="1862-03-12">March 12, 1862.</date><lb />special orders, <num value="42">no. 42</num>.</head> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="75" /> <num value="3">III</num>.

<milestone unit="sentence" n="76" />The municipal laws regulating charges for the hire of hacks, wagons, and drays, will be rigidly enforced. </p> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="77" /> All hacks, wagons, and drays will post, in some conspicuous place about their vehicles, the list of rates allowed by law, and any driver charging more than those rates, will be imprisoned, and the license withdrawn. </p> <closer> <signed><persName n="Winder,,John,H.,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00043" reg="default:Winder,John,H.,," authname="winder,john,h."><foreName full="yes">John</foreName> <foreName full="yes">H.</foreName>  <surname full="yes">Winder</surname></persName>,</signed> <lb /> <rs type="role" reg="Brigadier-General">Brig.-Gen.</rs> Commanding, &amp;c. <lb /> mh <num value="13">13</num>--6t </closer> </div3> 
<div3 type="orders" n="17" org="uniform" sample="complete"> 
<head>Attention, young men of <placeName key="tgn,7013964" n="1.000 11" reg="richmond, richmond, virginia" authname="tgn,7013964">Richmond</placeName>!</head> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="78" /> Having been detailed to recruit for the <hi rend="italics"><orgName type="regiment" key="1VAVolunteer">First Regiment Virginia Volunteers</orgName>,</hi> (now stationed at <placeName reg="Centreville, Fairfax, Virginia" key="tgn,2111026" authname="tgn,2111026">Centreville</placeName>,) a bounty of <measure n="50dollars" type="currency">fifty Dollars</measure>, uniform and subsistence, will be gives to all able-bodied young men who may enlist in this, <hi rend="italics">the oldest volunteer regiment in the <rs>Confederates States</rs>.</hi> </p> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="79" /> For further particulars apply at the recruiting station, <num value="3">No. 3</num>, <address><street n="10 Street">10th street</street></address>, between <address><street n="Main street">Main</street></address> and <address><street n="Cary street">Cary</street></address> streets. </p> <closer> <signed><persName n="Harrison,,W.,W.,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00044" reg="default:Harrison,W.,W.,," authname="harrison,w.,w."><foreName full="yes">W.</foreName> <foreName full="yes">W.</foreName>  <surname full="yes">Harrison</surname></persName>,</signed> <lb /> <rs type="role2">Lieutenant</rs> and Recruiting Officer. <lb /> P. S.--<num value="2">Two</num> new companies will be received, as there are at present but <num value="8">eight</num> in the regiment. [mh <num value="3">3</num>--ts] W. W. H. <lb /> </closer> </div3> 
<div3 type="orders" n="18" org="uniform" sample="complete"> 
<head>Attention!</head> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="80" /> The undersigned propose to raise a company of <orgName type="mil" key="LightArtillery">Light Artillery</orgName> to be enlisted for the war. We are happy now to announce that we have procured the guns, which will be ready for us, together with all equipments, as soon as our company is mustered into service.

<milestone unit="sentence" n="81" />To those who would like to go along with us and share with us the fortunes of this war, we earnestly appeal to come forward now and join us at office.

<milestone unit="sentence" n="82" />Besides the bounty of <measure n="50dollars" type="currency">$50</measure>, uniforms, board and lodgings will be furnished free.

<milestone unit="sentence" n="83" />Application may be made at our <placeName reg="Recruiting office">Recruiting office</placeName>, on <address><street n="Main Street">Main</street></address>, between <address><street n="7 Street">7th</street></address> and <address><street n="8 Street">8th streets</street></address>, or at the store of <persName n="Johnston,,,,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00045" reg="nearbymention:Johnston,Peyton,,," authname="johnston,peyton"><surname full="yes">Johnston</surname></persName> &amp; <persName n="Bransford,,,,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00046" reg="nearbymention:Bransford,John,W.,," authname="bransford,john,w."><surname full="yes">Bransford</surname></persName>. </p> <closer> <signed><persName n="Johnson,,Marmaduke,,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00047" reg="default:Johnson,Marmaduke,,," authname="johnson,marmaduke"><foreName full="yes">Marmaduke</foreName>  <surname full="yes">Johnson</surname></persName>,</signed> <lb /> <signed><persName n="Bransford,,John,W.,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00048" reg="default:Bransford,John,W.,," authname="bransford,john,w."><foreName full="yes">John</foreName> <foreName full="yes">W.</foreName>  <surname full="yes">Bransford</surname></persName>.</signed> <lb /> fe <num value="26">26</num>--ts <signed><persName n="Guigon,,A.,B.,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00049" reg="default:Guigon,A.,B.,," authname="guigon,a.,b."><foreName full="yes">A.</foreName> <foreName full="yes">B.</foreName>  <surname full="yes">Guigon</surname></persName>.</signed> </closer> </div3> 
<div3 type="orders" n="19" org="uniform" sample="complete"> 
<head><orgName n="War Department" type="department">War Department</orgName>,<hi rend="smallcaps">Adj't and Insp'r Gen.'s office,</hi> <placeName key="tgn,7013964" n="1.000 11" reg="richmond, richmond, virginia" authname="tgn,7013964">Richmond</placeName>, <date value="1862-03-13" authname="1862-03-13">March 13, 1862.</date> <lb /><sic>Genral</sic> orders, <num value="14">no. 14</num>.</head> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="84" /> <persName n="Lee,General,Robert,E.,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00050" reg="default:Lee,Robert,E.,," authname="lee,robert,e."><roleName n="General" full="yes">General</roleName> <foreName full="yes">Robert</foreName> <foreName full="yes">E.</foreName> <surname full="yes">Lee</surname></persName> is assigned to duty at the seat of Government; and <unclear>unper</unclear> the direction of the <rs>President</rs> is charged with the conduct of military operations in the armies of the <rs>Confederacy</rs>. </p> <closer> By order of <signed>the <rs type="role" reg="Secretary of War">Secretary of War</rs>.</signed> <lb /> <signed>[Signed]</signed> <signed><persName n="Cooper,,S.,,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00051" reg="default:Cooper,S.,,," authname="cooper,s."><foreName full="yes">S.</foreName>  <surname full="yes">Cooper</surname></persName>,</signed> <lb /> mh <num value="14">14</num>--1w Adj't and Insp'r Gen'l. </closer> </div3> 
<div3 type="orders" n="20" org="uniform" sample="complete"> 
<head>Attention, Artillery!

<milestone unit="sentence" n="85" /><num value="30">thirty</num> Recruits wanted.</head> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="86" /> We are authorized by the <rs>Governor</rs> to raise a <orgName type="mil" key="CompanyArtillery">Company of Artillery</orgName>.

<milestone unit="sentence" n="87" />Apply to <persName n="Bayly,Colonel,S.,T.,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00052" reg="expanded:Bayly,Samuel,T.,," authname="bayly,samuel,t."><roleName n="Colonel" full="yes">Colonel</roleName> <foreName full="yes">S.</foreName> <foreName full="yes">T.</foreName> <surname full="yes">Bayly</surname></persName>, at the <orgName>office of Bayly</orgName> -- <persName n="White,,,,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00053" reg="mostcommon:White,Charles,O.,,:1" authname="white,charles,o."><surname full="yes">White</surname></persName>, <placeName key="tgn,7013964" n="1.000 11" reg="richmond, richmond, virginia" authname="tgn,7013964">Richmond</placeName>, <persName n="Winn,Colonel,William,R.,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00054" reg="default:Winn,William,R.,," authname="winn,william,r."><roleName n="Colonel" full="yes">Col.</roleName> <foreName n="William" full="yes">Wm.</foreName> <foreName full="yes">R.</foreName> <surname full="yes">Winn</surname></persName>, <placeName reg="Ashland, Hanover, Virginia" key="tgn,2110477" authname="tgn,2110477">Ashland</placeName>, and to <persName n="Williams,Sergeant,J.,A.,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00055" reg="default:Williams,J.,A.,," authname="williams,j.,a."><roleName n="Sergeant" full="yes">Sergeant</roleName> <foreName full="yes">J.</foreName> <foreName full="yes">A.</foreName> <surname full="yes">Williams</surname></persName>, Recruiting Officer, <placeName reg="Chesterfield, Chesterfield, Virginia" key="tgn,2111165" authname="tgn,2111165">Chesterfield</placeName>.

<milestone unit="sentence" n="88" />We have authority to enlist militiamen until they are mustered into actual service. </p> <closer> <signed><persName n="Bayly,,Samuel,T.,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00056" reg="default:Bayly,Samuel,T.,," authname="bayly,samuel,t."><foreName full="yes">Samuel</foreName> <foreName full="yes">T.</foreName>  <surname full="yes">Bayly</surname></persName>,</signed> <lb /> <rs type="role">Capt.</rs> Co."A." <num value="20" type="ordinal">20th</num> Regt <orgName type="mil" key="VAVolunteer">Va. Vols.</orgName> <lb /> <signed><persName n="Winn,,William,R.,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00057" reg="default:Winn,William,R.,," authname="winn,william,r."><foreName n="William" full="yes">Wm.</foreName> <foreName full="yes">R.</foreName>  <surname full="yes">Winn</surname></persName>.</signed> <lb /> mh <num value="14">14</num>--8t* <rs type="role">Col.</rs> <num value="76" type="ordinal">76th</num> Reg't <orgName type="mil" key="VAMilitia">Va. Militia</orgName>. </closer> </div3> 
<div3 type="orders" n="21" org="uniform" sample="complete"> 
<head type="nobreak">Militia, attention</head> 
<p rend="nobreak">

<milestone unit="sentence" n="89" /> --I am authorized by the <rs type="role" reg="Secretary of War">Secretary of War</rs> to raise a Company of <orgName type="mil" key="HvArtillery">Heavy Artillery</orgName>, to be attached to <orgName n="Battalion"><persName n="Morriss,,,,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00058" reg="nearbymention:Morriss,Robert,F.,," authname="morriss,robert,f."><surname full="yes">Morriss</surname></persName>'s Battalion</orgName>. </p> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="90" /> The usual bounty of <measure n="50dollars" type="currency">$50</measure> will be paid when the roll is signed and the volunteers swore in. </p> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="91" /> Call at <persName n="Starke,,P.,H.,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00059" reg="default:Starke,P.,H.,," authname="starke,p.,h."><foreName full="yes">P.</foreName> <foreName full="yes">H.</foreName> <surname full="yes">Starke</surname></persName>'s, <address><street n="Main street">Main</street></address>, between <address><street n="14 Street">14th</street></address> and <address><street n="15 Street">15th streets</street></address>, for the present. </p> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="92" /> Any militiaman can come in sign the roll take the bounty, and be <unclear>exempt.</unclear> </p> <closer> mh <num value="14">14</num>--<unclear /> <signed><persName n="Starke,,H.,W.,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00060" reg="default:Starke,H.,W.,," authname="starke,h.,w."><foreName full="yes">H.</foreName> <foreName full="yes">W.</foreName>  <surname full="yes">Starke</surname></persName>, <rs type="role2">Captain</rs>.</signed> </closer> </div3> <milestone unit="column" n="3" /> 
<div3 type="orders" n="22" org="uniform" sample="complete"> 
<head>Attention — <persName n="Boggs,,,,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00061" reg="mostcommon:Boggs,nomatch:0" authname="boggs"><surname full="yes">Boggs</surname></persName>'s<lb />Battalion <orgName n="Flying Artillery" type="artillery">flying Artillery</orgName>.</head> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="93" /> The undersigned having authority to raise a Company to form a part of this splendid corps, for which the most approved light Rifled <unclear /> are now being turned out, all those wishing to join a select company, and avoid the militia, will do well to enroll themselves at once, as the ranks are filling rapidly.

<milestone unit="sentence" n="94" />The special attention of the militia is invited to the fact that we are authorized to give the most positive assurance that no man enlisting in this company remains liable either to the present call of the <rs>Governor</rs>, or to any future draft upon the militia.

<milestone unit="sentence" n="95" />Who will wait to be a drafted militiaman? </p> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="96" /> Apply at Recruiting <orgName>Office of the Battalion</orgName>, <address><street n="Bank street">Bank street</street></address>, near corner of <num value="12" type="ordinal">12th</num>. </p> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="97" /> Bounty down--<hi rend="smallcaps"><measure n="50dollars" type="currency">Fifty Dollars</measure>.</hi> </p> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="98" /> We refer particularly to <persName n="Boggs,Major,,,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00062" reg="mostcommon:Boggs,nomatch:0" authname="boggs"><roleName n="Major" full="yes">Major</roleName> <surname full="yes">Boggs</surname></persName>'s card calling on those who wish to enter his corps, to report to the officers of this company. </p> <closer> <signed><persName n="Martin,,S.,Taylor,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00063" reg="default:Martin,S.,Taylor,," authname="martin,s.,taylor"><foreName full="yes">S.</foreName> <foreName full="yes">Taylor</foreName>  <surname full="yes">Martin</surname></persName>,</signed> <lb /> <orgName type="regiment" key="1CompanyHowitzers">1st Company Howitzers</orgName>, <lb /> <signed>Alex'r <persName n="Holladay,,Q.,,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00064" reg="default:Holladay,Q.,,," authname="holladay,q."><foreName full="yes">Q.</foreName> <surname full="yes">Holladay</surname></persName>,</signed> <lb /> <rs type="role">Lieut.</rs> <orgName type="regiment" key="Regiment 20">20th Regt.</orgName> <orgName type="mil" key="VAVolunteer">Va. Vols.</orgName> <signed><persName n="Garnett,,William,F.,G.," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00065" reg="default:Garnett,William,F.,G.," authname="garnett,william,f.,g."><foreName n="William" full="yes">Wm.</foreName> <foreName full="yes">F.</foreName>  <foreName full="yes">G.</foreName>  <surname full="yes">Garnett</surname>, <genName n="junior" full="yes">Jr.</genName></persName>,</signed> <lb /> <orgName n="Fayette Artillery" type="artillery">Fayette Artillery</orgName>. <lb /> <signed><persName n="Bolling,,Richard,M.,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00066" reg="default:Bolling,Richard,M.,," authname="bolling,richard,m."><foreName full="yes">Richard</foreName> <foreName full="yes">M.</foreName>  <surname full="yes">Bolling</surname></persName>,</signed> <lb /> <placeName reg="Goochland, Virginia, United States" key="tgn,2002163" authname="tgn,2002163">Goochland</placeName> <orgName type="mil" key="LightDragoon">Light Dragoons</orgName>. <lb /> N. B.--None but men of good character need apply. mh <num value="12">12</num>--8t* </closer> </div3> 
<div3 type="orders" n="23" org="uniform" sample="complete"> 
<head type="nobreak">Attention, Volunteers.</head> 
<p rend="nobreak">

<milestone unit="sentence" n="99" /> --It will be seen by the following proclamation that persons who prefer to volunteer rather than be subjected to the discredit of the militia draft, can do so by coming forward now and declaring their willingness to serve their country of their own accord. </p> 
<div4 type="entry" n="1" org="uniform" sample="complete"> 
<head /> <opener> <dateline> <name type="place"><orgName n="Department of the Executive" type="government">Executive Department</orgName>, Va.,</name> <date value="1862-03-11" authname="1862-03-11">March 11th, 1862.</date> </dateline> </opener> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="100" /> The commandants of companies of volunteers, an'horiged to be raised by the <rs>Governor</rs>, which are not yet completed are hereby permitted to fill up their command by volunteers from the militia of the <rs>State</rs> until the militia are mustered into service.

<milestone unit="sentence" n="101" />No substitutes will be allowed. </p> <closer> By order of <signed>the <rs>Governor</rs>.</signed> <signed><persName n="Frence,,S.,Bassett,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00067" reg="default:Frence,S.,Bassett,," authname="frence,s.,bassett"><foreName full="yes">S.</foreName> <foreName full="yes">Bassett</foreName>  <surname full="yes">Frence</surname></persName>,</signed> <lb /> <rs type="role" reg="Aide de camp">Aide-de-camp</rs>. <lb /> It will thus be seen that the alternative presented now is, whether <persName n="Virginians,,,,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00068" reg="mostcommon:Virginians,nomatch:0" authname="virginians"><surname full="yes">Virginians</surname></persName> will volunteer to defend the <rs>Southern</rs> cause, or be subjected into service by force. As will be seen, this choice must be made at once. Will not the sons of <placeName reg="Virginia, United States, North and Central America" key="tgn,7007919" authname="tgn,7007919">Virginia</placeName> now come forward and enlist their named.--Apply at our office, in the <rs type="place">Whig Building</rs>. <lb /> <signed><persName n="Johnson,,Marmaduke,,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00069" reg="default:Johnson,Marmaduke,,," authname="johnson,marmaduke"><foreName full="yes">Marmaduke</foreName>  <surname full="yes">Johnson</surname></persName>,</signed> <lb /> <signed><persName n="Bransford,,John,W.,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00070" reg="default:Bransford,John,W.,," authname="bransford,john,w."><foreName full="yes">John</foreName> <foreName full="yes">W.</foreName>  <surname full="yes">Bransford</surname></persName>,</signed> <lb /> <signed><persName n="Guigon,,A.,B.,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00071" reg="default:Guigon,A.,B.,," authname="guigon,a.,b."><foreName full="yes">A.</foreName> <foreName full="yes">B.</foreName>  <surname full="yes">Guigon</surname></persName>.</signed> <lb /> mh <num value="12">12</num>--ts <signed><persName n="Clutter,,V.,J.,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00072" reg="default:Clutter,V.,J.,," authname="clutter,v.,j."><foreName full="yes">V.</foreName> <foreName full="yes">J.</foreName>  <surname full="yes">Clutter</surname></persName>.</signed> </closer> </div4> </div3> 
<div3 type="orders" n="24" org="uniform" sample="complete"> 
<head>Headq'rs Dep't of <placeName reg="Henrico, Virginia, United States" key="tgn,1002467" authname="tgn,1002467">Henrico</placeName>, <placeName reg="Richmond, Richmond, Virginia" key="tgn,7013964" authname="tgn,7013964">Richmond, Va.</placeName>, <date value="1862-03-11" authname="1862-03-11">March 11, 1862.</date> <lb />General orders, <num value="6">no. 6</num>.</head> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="102" /> <num value="2">II</num>.

<milestone unit="sentence" n="103" />Railroad companies are forbidden to transport into this city or out of it, spirituous liquors or other intoxicating beverages. </p> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="104" /> <num value="3">III</num>.

<milestone unit="sentence" n="105" />Superintendents of railroads are requested to report daily to the <rs type="role" reg="Provost Marshal">Provost Marshal</rs> the number of passengers passing over their roads out of the city of <placeName key="tgn,7013964" n="1.000 11" reg="richmond, richmond, virginia" authname="tgn,7013964">Richmond</placeName>. </p> <closer> By order of <lb /> <signed><rs type="role">Brig.</rs><persName n="Winder,General,Jonathan,H.,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00073" reg="default:Winder,Jonathan,H.,," authname="winder,jonathan,h."><roleName n="General" full="yes">Gen'l</roleName> <foreName n="Jonathan" full="yes">Jno.</foreName> <foreName full="yes">H.</foreName> <surname full="yes">Winder</surname></persName>, <rs type="role">Com.</rs> &amp;c.</signed> <lb /> mh <num value="13">13</num>--ts <signed><persName n="Page,,L.,R.,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00074" reg="default:Page,L.,R.,," authname="page,l.,r."><foreName full="yes">L.</foreName> <foreName full="yes">R.</foreName>  <surname full="yes">Page</surname></persName>, <persName n="Gen,,A.,A.,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00075" reg="default:Gen,A.,A.,," authname="gen,a.,a."><foreName full="yes">A.</foreName> <foreName full="yes">A.</foreName> <surname full="yes">Gen</surname></persName>'l.</signed> </closer> </div3> 
<div3 type="orders" n="25" org="uniform" sample="complete"> 
<head>Headq'rs <persName n="Grays,,Elliott,,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00076" reg="default:Grays,Elliott,,," authname="grays,elliott"><foreName full="yes">Elliott</foreName> <surname full="yes">Grays</surname></persName>, <hi rend="smallcaps"><placeName reg="Louisville, Jefferson, Kentucky" key="tgn,7013915" authname="tgn,7013915">Fort Nelson</placeName>,</hi> <placeName reg="Norfolk harbor">Norfolk harbor</placeName>, <date value="1862-03" authname="1862-03">March --, 1862.</date></head> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="106" /> this well-known company having determined to remain in the service, is desirous of increasing the number of enlisted men to <num value="125">125</num>.

<milestone unit="sentence" n="107" />A <placeName reg="Recruiting Office">Recruiting Office</placeName> has been opened for that purpose at the store of <persName n="Bossieux,,Louis,J.,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00077" reg="default:Bossieux,Louis,J.,," authname="bossieux,louis,j."><foreName full="yes">Louis</foreName> <foreName full="yes">J.</foreName> <surname full="yes">Bossieux</surname></persName>, <address><street n="Main Street 80">80 Main street</street></address>, and also at the store of <persName n="Butler,,Joseph,,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00078" reg="default:Butler,Joseph,,," authname="butler,joseph"><foreName full="yes">Joseph</foreName> <surname full="yes">Butler</surname></persName>, town of <placeName reg="Richmond, Richmond, Virginia" key="tgn,7013964" authname="tgn,7013964">Manchester</placeName>.

<milestone unit="sentence" n="108" />All young men who are disposed to volunteer can learn the particulars of the condition and organization of the company from <persName n="Fitzgerald,Lieutenant,Henry,,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00079" reg="default:Fitzgerald,Henry,,," authname="fitzgerald,henry"><roleName n="Lieutenant" full="yes">Lieut.</roleName> <foreName full="yes">Henry</foreName> <surname full="yes">Fitzgerald</surname></persName>, who can be found at either place of rendezvous. </p> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="109" /> Recruits are entitled to pay, transportation, and subsistence, from the time and place of enrollment, and also to the bounty of <measure n="50dollars" type="currency">fifty dollars</measure>. </p> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="110" /> I hope that this call may meet with a speedy response, and that I may never be a witness to the drafting of young men from the districts in the neighborhood of <placeName key="tgn,7013964" n="1.000 11" reg="richmond, richmond, virginia" authname="tgn,7013964">Richmond</placeName>.

<milestone unit="sentence" n="111" />All recruits are to be persons of good character, and men in whom I can place implicit confidence. </p> <closer> <signed><persName n="Bossieux,,Louis,F.,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00080" reg="default:Bossieux,Louis,F.,," authname="bossieux,louis,f."><foreName full="yes">Louis</foreName> <foreName full="yes">F.</foreName>  <surname full="yes">Bossieux</surname></persName>.</signed> <lb /> <persName n="Grays,Captain,Elliott,,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00081" reg="default:Grays,Elliott,,," authname="grays,elliott"><roleName n="Captain" full="yes">Captain</roleName> <foreName full="yes">Elliott</foreName> <surname full="yes">Grays</surname></persName>. <lb /> <signed><persName n="Fitzgerald,,Henry,,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00082" reg="default:Fitzgerald,Henry,,," authname="fitzgerald,henry"><foreName full="yes">Henry</foreName>  <surname full="yes">Fitzgerald</surname></persName>,</signed> <rs type="role">Lieut.</rs>, Recruiting Officer mh <num value="10">10</num>--ts </closer> </div3> 
<div3 type="orders" n="26" org="uniform" sample="complete"> 
<head type="nobreak"><orgName n="Richmond Fayette Artillery" type="artillery">Richmond Fayette Artillery</orgName></head> 
<p rend="nobreak">

<milestone unit="sentence" n="112" /> --Having re-organized and re-enlisted for <measure n="2years" type="date">two years</measure>, is desirous of receiving <num value="40">forty</num> additional recruits, to raise the company to the number of <num value="150">one hundred and fifty</num>.

<milestone unit="sentence" n="113" />The battery is composed of <num value="4">four</num> brass <num value="6">six</num>-pounders and <num value="2">two</num> rifle guns, and is among the finest in the <orgName n="Confederate Army" type="org">Confederate Army</orgName>.

<milestone unit="sentence" n="114" />The <orgName n="Fayette Artillery" type="artillery">Fayette Artillery</orgName> is <num value="1">one</num> of the best equipped companies in the service.

<milestone unit="sentence" n="115" />A liberal bounty will be given to each recruit.

<milestone unit="sentence" n="116" />Only men of respectability, courage, and patriotism, are, however, required.

<milestone unit="sentence" n="117" />For further particulars, apply to <persName n="Johnston,,Peyton,,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00083" reg="default:Johnston,Peyton,,," authname="johnston,peyton"><foreName full="yes">Peyton</foreName> <surname full="yes">Johnston</surname></persName>, <address><street n="Main Street 115">115 Main street</street></address> <placeName key="tgn,7013964" n="1.000 11" reg="richmond, richmond, virginia" authname="tgn,7013964">Richmond</placeName>, or to the undersigned, at <placeName reg="Yorktown, York, Virginia" key="tgn,2115169" authname="tgn,2115169">Yorktown</placeName>. </p> <closer> <signed><persName n="Macon,,M.,C.,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00084" reg="default:Macon,M.,C.,," authname="macon,m.,c."><foreName full="yes">M.</foreName> <foreName full="yes">C.</foreName>  <surname full="yes">Macon</surname></persName>,</signed> <lb /> mh <num value="12">12</num>--st <rs type="role2">Capt</rs>. R. F. A. </closer> </div3> 
<div3 type="orders" n="27" org="uniform" sample="complete"> 
<head type="nobreak">Notice.</head> 
<p rend="nobreak">

<milestone unit="sentence" n="118" /> --The <orgName type="regiment" key="2Company">Second Company</orgName> of Richmond Howitzers has been reorganized, and <persName n="Watson,Lieutenant,David,,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00085" reg="default:Watson,David,,," authname="watson,david"><roleName n="Lieutenant" full="yes">Lieutenant</roleName> <foreName full="yes">David</foreName> <surname full="yes">Watson</surname></persName> elected <rs type="role2">Captain</rs>.

<milestone unit="sentence" n="119" />We are anxious to increase the number of our Company to <num value="120">120</num>.

<milestone unit="sentence" n="120" />An opportunity is thus offered to young men of good moral character to join an old organization, which has <num value="2">two</num> rifles and <num value="2">two</num> howitzers, and is thoroughly equipped for field service. </p> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="121" /> Apply to <persName n="Pleasants,,R.,B.,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00086" reg="default:Pleasants,R.,B.,," authname="pleasants,r.,b."><foreName full="yes">R.</foreName> <foreName full="yes">B.</foreName> <surname full="yes">Pleasants</surname></persName> or <persName n="Jones,,Henry,S.,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00087" reg="default:Jones,Henry,S.,," authname="jones,henry,s."><foreName full="yes">Henry</foreName> <foreName full="yes">S.</foreName> <surname full="yes">Jones</surname></persName>, <num value="7">No. 7</num>, <address><street n="Wall street">Wall street</street></address>, under <placeName reg="St. Charles Hotel">St. Charles Hotel</placeName>; or <persName n="Wellford,,William,N.,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00088" reg="default:Wellford,William,N.,," authname="wellford,william,n."><foreName n="William" full="yes">Wm.</foreName> <foreName full="yes">N.</foreName> <surname full="yes">Wellford</surname></persName>, <hi rend="smallcaps">Jr.,</hi> <placeName reg="Brandy Station, Culpeper, Virginia" key="tgn,2110767" authname="tgn,2110767">Brandy Station, Culpeper county, Virginia</placeName>, or <persName n="Christian,,George,L.,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00089" reg="default:Christian,George,L.,," authname="christian,george,l."><foreName n="George" full="yes">Geo.</foreName> <foreName full="yes">L.</foreName> <surname full="yes">Christian</surname></persName>, <placeName reg="Charles City Court House">Charles City C. H.</placeName>, <placeName reg="Virginia" key="tgn,7007919" authname="tgn,7007919">Virginia</placeName>.

<milestone unit="sentence" n="122" />mh <num value="10">10</num>--14t* </p> </div3> 
<div3 type="orders" n="28" org="uniform" sample="complete"> 
<head><placeName reg="United States" key="tgn,7012149" authname="tgn,7012149">Confederate States of America</placeName>, <hi rend="smallcaps">Quartermaster's office,</hi> <placeName reg="Richmond, Richmond, Virginia" key="tgn,7013964" authname="tgn,7013964">Richmond, Va.</placeName>, <date value="1862-03-07" authname="1862-03-07">7th March, 1862.</date></head> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="123" /> to Railroads.--To facilitate the transfer of Recruits from Recruiting stations to their Regiments, officers of railroad companies are notified that the <rs>Recruiting Officers</rs> are authorized to give orders of transportation for their recruits, and such orders or certificates of transportation given by the persons in charge of the recruits, will be acknowledged as sufficient vouchers for payment. </p> <closer> <signed><persName n="Smith,,Larkin,,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00090" reg="default:Smith,Larkin,,," authname="smith,larkin"><foreName full="yes">Larkin</foreName>  <surname full="yes">Smith</surname></persName>.</signed> <lb /> mh <num value="8">8</num>--10t Ass't Q. M. <rs type="role">Gen.</rs> </closer> </div3> 
<div3 type="orders" n="29" org="uniform" sample="complete"> 
<head><orgName type="mil" key="LightArtillery">Light Artillery</orgName>!! <lb />Battery secured!!! <lb />bounty <measure n="50dollars" type="currency">fifty Dollars</measure>!</head> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="124" /> The undersigned having secured a splendid battery of field pieces, have authority to raise a Company of <orgName type="mil" key="LightArtillery">Light Artillery</orgName>, to be mustered into the service of the <orgName n="Provisional Army" type="misc">Provisional Army of <placeName reg="Virginia, United States, North and Central America" key="tgn,7007919" authname="tgn,7007919">Virginia</placeName></orgName>.

<milestone unit="sentence" n="125" />for the war. Each man will be entitled to a bounty of <measure n="50dollars" type="currency">$50</measure> upon being mustered in. As an opportunity of enlisting in this arm of the service will not hereafter be of frequent occurrence, those wishing to join will make application at, once at the rendezvous, northwest corner of <persName n="Cary,,,,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00091" reg="mostcommon:Cary,nomatch:0" authname="cary"><surname full="yes">Cary</surname></persName> and <unclear>1th</unclear> streets, where <num value="1">one</num> or more of the undersigned can always be seen. </p> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="126" /> Those having substitutes will seed them in at once, as the ranks are filling rapidly. </p> <closer> <signed><persName n="Crutchfield,,Stapleton,,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00092" reg="default:Crutchfield,Stapleton,,," authname="crutchfield,stapleton"><foreName full="yes">Stapleton</foreName>  <surname full="yes">Crutchfield</surname></persName>,</signed> <lb /> <signed><persName n="Tanner,,William,E.,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00093" reg="default:Tanner,William,E.,," authname="tanner,william,e."><foreName full="yes">William</foreName> <foreName full="yes">E.</foreName>  <surname full="yes">Tanner</surname></persName>,</signed> <lb /> <signed><persName n="Wortham,,Charles,E.,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00094" reg="default:Wortham,Charles,E.,," authname="wortham,charles,e."><foreName full="yes">Charles</foreName> <foreName full="yes">E.</foreName>  <surname full="yes">Wortham</surname></persName>.</signed> <lb /> fe <num value="18">18</num>--ts </closer> </div3> 
<div3 type="orders" n="30" org="uniform" sample="complete"> 
<head type="nobreak"><orgName type="mil" key="LightArtillery">Light Artillery</orgName></head> 
<p rend="nobreak">

<milestone unit="sentence" n="127" /> --The present condition of our country seems to us to require the services of all who are capable of bearing arms and in a situation to leave home.

<milestone unit="sentence" n="128" />We have therefore obtained from the <rs type="role" reg="Secretary of War">Secretary of War</rs> authority to raise a company of <orgName type="mil" key="LightArtillery">Light Artillery</orgName>, and call upon our fellow-citizens to come forward and aid us in getting it up. </p> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="129" /> We want, if possible, to raise a company sufficient to man a battery of <num value="6">six</num> guns, and think this enterprise offers a fine opportunity to all who wish to volunteer, and thus save themselves from a draft in the militia. </p> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="130" /> <persName n="Gray,,,,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00095" reg="mostcommon:Gray,John,H.,,:1" authname="gray,john,h."><surname full="yes">Gray</surname></persName> uniform, of the <orgName n="Crenshaw Woolen Company" type="company">Crenshaw Woolen Company</orgName> Goods, will be furnished free, and the bounty of <measure n="50dollars" type="currency">$50</measure> paid to each man when the company is mustered in. </p> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="131" /> Rendezvous at the warehouse on the <name>Basin</name> bank, next door to <orgName><persName n="Crenshaw,,,,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00096" reg="nearbymention:Crenshaw,William,G.,," authname="crenshaw,william,g."><surname full="yes">Crenshaw</surname></persName> &amp; Co</orgName>'s, where <num value="1">one</num> of the undersigned may always be found, and recruits maintained free of all expense. </p> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="132" /> The traveling expenses of recruits from the country to the city will be paid. </p> <closer> <signed><persName n="Crenshaw,,William,G.,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00097" reg="default:Crenshaw,William,G.,," authname="crenshaw,william,g."><foreName full="yes">William</foreName> <foreName full="yes">G.</foreName>  <surname full="yes">Crenshaw</surname></persName>,</signed> <lb /> <signed><persName n="Ellett,,James,,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00098" reg="default:Ellett,James,,," authname="ellett,james"><foreName full="yes">James</foreName>  <surname full="yes">Ellett</surname></persName>,</signed> <lb /> <signed><persName n="Hobson,,Charles,L.,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00099" reg="default:Hobson,Charles,L.,," authname="hobson,charles,l."><foreName full="yes">Charles</foreName> <foreName full="yes">L.</foreName>  <surname full="yes">Hobson</surname></persName>,</signed> <lb /> fe <num value="18">18</num>--ts <signed><persName n="Johnston,,Andrew,B.,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00100" reg="default:Johnston,Andrew,B.,," authname="johnston,andrew,b."><foreName full="yes">Andrew</foreName> <foreName full="yes">B.</foreName>  <surname full="yes">Johnston</surname></persName>.</signed> </closer> </div3> 
<div3 type="orders" n="31" org="uniform" sample="complete"> 
<head>Recruits wanted--<num value="40">40</num> Volunteers to fill up the <orgName n="Virginia Life Guard" type="guard">Virginia life Guard</orgName>.</head> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="133" /> Being ordered on recruiting service.

<milestone unit="sentence" n="134" />I will receive new members for the above company at my office, near Shockoe Warehouse, between <num value="10">10</num> o'clk A. M. and <time value="2pm">2 P. M.</time> This company was among the <num value="1" type="ordinal">first</num> in the field, and are re-enlisting for the war. Acquaintances of the present members of the company who prefer being in association with their friends to being drafted, will do well to volunteer <hi rend="italics">at once</hi> in this company. </p> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="135" /> Substitutes will not be received. </p> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="136" /> arms — Enfield Rifles. </p> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="137" /> The usual bounty &amp;c., given. </p> <closer> <signed><persName n="Walker,,Jonathan,Stewart,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00101" reg="default:Walker,Jonathan,Stewart,," authname="walker,jonathan,stewart"><foreName n="Jonathan" full="yes">Jno.</foreName> <foreName full="yes">Stewart</foreName>  <surname full="yes">Walker</surname></persName>,</signed> <lb /> mh <num value="10">10</num>--9t* <rs type="role2">Captain</rs> <orgName n="Virginia Life Guard" type="guard">Virginia Life Guard</orgName>. </closer> </div3> 
<div3 type="orders" n="32" org="uniform" sample="complete"> 
<head type="nobreak">Naval medical Board of examination.</head> 
<p rend="nobreak">

<milestone unit="sentence" n="138" /> --A Board of Naval Surgeons is in session in this city, by order of the <orgName n="Navy Department" type="department">Navy Department</orgName>, for the examination of candidates for admission in the naval service of the <placeName reg="United States" key="tgn,7012149" authname="tgn,7012149">Confederate States</placeName> as assistant surgeons during the war. </p> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="139" /> The age of the candidate must not be less than <num value="21">twenty-one</num> nor more than <measure n="30years" type="date">thirty years</measure>. </p> <closer> <signed><persName n="Cornile,,James,,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00102" reg="default:Cornile,James,,," authname="cornile,james"><foreName full="yes">James</foreName>  <surname full="yes">Cornile</surname></persName>,</signed> <rs type="role2">President</rs>. <lb /> mh <num value="13">13</num>--2w </closer> </div3> </div2> <milestone unit="column" n="4" /> 
